      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 65: The RTT component uses absolute RTT, not RTT excess over a baseline, even though the config comment says `congestionRttScale` maps RTT excess. With the current defaults, a stable 300 ms path contributes 0.3 to the score and crosses the 0.08 threshold with no packet loss, causing repeated decreases on high-latency but uncongested links. Add a baseline RTT field or remove RTT from congestion until a baseline is established.\\n```suggestion\\n    float rttComponent \u003d std::max(0.0f, (ewmaRtt_ - cfg_.baselineRttMs) / cfg_.congestionRttScale);\\n```",
      "revId": "34b6e0f385d13adb7d6f41c2949a9d5b8b49f1ab",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
