      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T08:10:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 133: `lastDecrease_` is initialized to `time_point::min()`, so `now - lastDecrease_` can overflow/produce an enormous duration before any decrease has occurred. That makes the first probing ramp jump straight to `maxIncreaseFactor`, allowing aggressive bitrate growth immediately after startup instead of the configured slow ramp. Handle the no-decrease case explicitly.\\n```suggestion\\n    float rampProgress \u003d 0.0f;\\n    if (lastDecrease_ !\u003d time_point::min()) {\\n        auto secSinceDecrease \u003d std::chrono::duration\u003cfloat\u003e(now - lastDecrease_).count();\\n        rampProgress \u003d std::clamp(\\n            (secSinceDecrease - cfg_.probeDelaySec) / cfg_.increaseRampTime, 0.0f, 1.0f);\\n    }\\n```",
      "revId": "34b6e0f385d13adb7d6f41c2949a9d5b8b49f1ab",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
