      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T08:10:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 649: REMB feedback updates the controller but the returned bitrate is never applied unless a Receiver Report is also available later in the same pass. This regresses the previous delay-based path where REMB overuse immediately reduced the encoder bitrate, and can leave video sending too high during congestion when RR packets are delayed or missing. Apply the controller result immediately.\\n```suggestion\\n        if (isOveruse || br \u003d\u003d 0x7378) {\\n            auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onRembFeedback(isOveruse);\\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\\n        }\\n```",
      "revId": "34b6e0f385d13adb7d6f41c2949a9d5b8b49f1ab",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
