      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 704: `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` now calls `bwController_.setTargetBitrate(codecVideo-\u003ebitrate)` every time it runs, and `adaptQualityAndBitrate()` calls it before each controller update. This resets `lastStableBitrate_` and the controller target to the codec bitrate on every RTCP tick, which undermines AIMD state and can also overwrite reductions made just before calling `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` (for example in `onAudioCongestion`). Sync limits each tick, but only seed the controller target on initialization/start or when the codec limits actually change.\\n```suggestion\\n        bwController_.setLimits(codecVideo-\u003eminBitrate, codecVideo-\u003emaxBitrate);\\n        // Do not reset the controller target on every RTCP check; it owns the current AIMD target.\\n```",
      "revId": "34b6e0f385d13adb7d6f41c2949a9d5b8b49f1ab",
